name: AzureServicebus
help: Manage Azure Service Bus namespaces, queues, topics, subscriptions, rules and geo-disaster recovery configuration alias.

properties.name: Name
properties.help: Name of Topic.

properties.name: NamespaceName
properties.help: Name of Namespace.

properties.name: ResourceGroup
properties.help: Name of resource group. You can configure the default group using `az configure --defaults group=&lt;name&gt;`.

properties.name: AutoDeleteOnIdle
properties.help: ISO 8601 timespan or duration time format for idle interval after which the topic is automatically deleted. The minimum duration is 5 minutes.

properties.name: DefaultMessageTimeToLive
properties.help: ISO 8601 or duration time format for Default message timespan to live value. This is the duration after which the message expires, starting from when the message is sent to Service Bus. This is the default value used when TimeToLive is not set on a message itself.

properties.name: DuplicateDetectionHistoryTimeWindow
properties.help: ISO 8601 timespan or duration time format for structure that defines the duration of the duplicate detection history. The default value is 10 minutes.

properties.name: EnableBatchedOperations
properties.help: Allow server-side batched operations.

properties.name: EnableDuplicateDetection
properties.help: A boolean value indicating if this topic requires duplicate detection.

properties.name: EnableExpress
properties.help: A boolean value that indicates whether Express Entities are enabled. An express topic holds a message in memory temporarily before writing it to persistent storage.

properties.name: EnableOrdering
properties.help: A boolean value that indicates whether the topic supports ordering.

properties.name: EnablePartitioning
properties.help: A boolean value that indicates whether the topic to be partitioned across multiple message brokers is enabled.

properties.name: MaxSize
properties.help: Maximum size of topic in megabytes, which is the size of the memory allocated for the topic. Default is 1024. Max for Standard SKU is 5120 and for Premium SKU is 81920.

properties.name: Status
properties.help: Enumerates the possible values for the status of a messaging entity.

properties.name: Subscription
properties.help: Name or ID of subscription. You can configure the default subscription using `az account set -s NAME_OR_ID`.

properties.name: AutoDeleteOnIdle
properties.help: ISO 8601 timeSpan or duration time format for idle interval after which the queue is automatically deleted. The minimum duration is 5 minutes.

properties.name: DefaultMessageTimeToLive
properties.help: ISO 8601 timespan or duration time format for default message to live value. This is the duration after which the message expires, starting from when the message is sent to Service Bus. This is the default value used when TimeToLive is not set on a message itself.

properties.name: DuplicateDetectionHistoryTimeWindow
properties.help: ISO 8601 timeSpan structure that defines the duration of the duplicate detection history. The default value is 10 minutes.

properties.name: EnableBatchedOperations
properties.help: Allow server-side batched operations.

properties.name: EnableDeadLetteringOnMessageExpiration
properties.help: A boolean value that indicates whether this queue has dead letter support when a message expires.

properties.name: EnableDuplicateDetection
properties.help: A boolean value indicating if this queue requires duplicate detection.

properties.name: EnableExpress
properties.help: A boolean value that indicates whether Express Entities are enabled. An express queue holds a message in memory temporarily before writing it to persistent storage.

properties.name: EnablePartitioning
properties.help: A boolean value that indicates whether the queue is to be partitioned across multiple message brokers.

properties.name: EnableSession
properties.help: A boolean value indicating whether the queue supports the concept of sessions.

properties.name: ForwardDeadLetteredMessagesTo
properties.help: Queue/Topic name to forward the Dead Letter message.

properties.name: ForwardTo
properties.help: Queue/Topic name to forward the messages.

properties.name: LockDuration
properties.help: String ISO 8601 timespan or duration format for duration of a peek-lock; that is, the amount of time that the message is locked for other receivers. The maximum value for LockDuration is 5 minutes; the default value is 1 minute.

properties.name: MaxDeliveryCount
properties.help: The maximum delivery count. A message is automatically deadlettered after this number of deliveries. default value is 10.

properties.name: MaxSize
properties.help: Maximum size of queue in megabytes, which is the size of the memory allocated for the queue. Default is 1024. Max for Standard SKU is 5120 and for Premium SKU is 81920.
